article.headline: High Point 103, Ferrum 61
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 27 points and led High Point to a 103-61 victory over Ferrum on Saturday. The High Point Panthers (4-2) held a 6-point lead at halftime, then started the second half with a 19-3 run and pulled away from the Ferrum Panthers (1-5). Reid was 11-for-13 from the floor with one 3-pointer, sank 4-of-4 from the line, and had 6 rebounds. High Point's second-leading scorer was Akeem Scott with 24 points. Ferrum enjoyed a lead as high as 8 points for much of the first half before losing control to High Point. Keith Harris hit 3-of-6 3-point shot attempts, and was the Ferrum Panthers' leading scorer with 16 points.
